Peru Stocks: Credicorp, Maple, Relapasa, Rio Alto, Rio Cristal

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-12-07T18:57:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/peru-stocks-credicorp-maple-relapasa-rio-alto-rio-cristal.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:30 p.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a second day, declining 0.6
percent to 19,975.24. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index  rose 0.3
percent to 2,571.87.  Industrial, banking and mining shares slumped as metals
declined in  New York  and  London , said Hernando Pastor, an
analyst at Lima-based Kallpa Securities SAB.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, dropped 8.3 percent to 11 cents.  Maple
Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer with
operations in Peru, fell 1.8 percent to $1.08.  Rio Alto Mining
Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company, declined 2.4
percent to $3.28.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest
financial-services company, slid 2.4 percent to $105.45.
 Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1)  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 1.1 percent to 91 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
